tasks and work flows:
If you don’t set a clear workflow early, team projects usually become chaos—duplicate work, broken code, last-minute stress. So let’s structure this properly from day one.

🚀 Team Workflow for Your Physiotherapy Project
👥 1. Define Roles (very important)

Even if everyone codes, assign primary responsibility:

Frontend Lead → React UI, dashboards
Backend Lead → APIs, logic (Node.js / Django)
Database Lead → schema, queries (PostgreSQL)
QA / Testing + Docs → testing + report + presentation

👉 Use:

GitHub for code collaboration
🔄 2. Development Workflow (simple & effective)
Step 1: Plan features

Break your project into modules:

Login system
Staff tracking
Performance analytics
Reports dashboard
Step 2: Use Task Board

Use:

Trello or
Jira

Create columns:

To Do
In Progress
Done

👉 Assign tasks to each member

Step 3: Git Workflow (must follow 🔥)

Use this structure in GitHub:

main → final working code
dev → testing branch
feature/* → each person’s work

Example:

feature/login
feature/dashboard

👉 Rule:

Never push directly to main
🔁 3. Daily Workflow (keep it simple)

Each day:

Pull latest code
Work on your feature
Push to your branch
Create Pull Request
Team reviews → merge
🧪 4. Integration Workflow (important)

Every 2–3 days:

Combine frontend + backend + database
Test full system

👉 Avoid “everything works separately but not together” problem

🗂️ 5. Folder Structure (clean project)
project/
 ├── frontend/ (React)
 ├── backend/ (Node.js)
 ├── database/ (SQL files)
 ├── docs/ (report, diagrams)
📊 6. Weekly Plan (easy timeline)
Week 1
Requirements + UI design
Database schema
Week 2
Backend APIs
Basic frontend
Week 3
Integration
Dashboard + analytics
Week 4
Testing
Final report + presentation
🧠 7. Communication (don’t ignore this)

Use:

WhatsApp (quick updates)
Google Meet (weekly meeting)

👉 Daily 5–10 min check:

What you did
What you will do
Any problem
⚠️ Common Mistakes (avoid these)

❌ Everyone doing same work
❌ No version control
❌ Last-minute integration
❌ No clear ownership

🏁 Final Simple Workflow (remember this)

👉 Plan → Assign → Develop → Review → Integrate → Test

💡 Pro Tip (to impress faculty)

Say this:

“We followed Agile methodology with Git-based version control and sprint-based development.”
